    <stitle>CLUTCH CONTROL LINKAGE - 2000, 4000, 7000, AND 8000 SERIES - MAINTENANCE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>MAINTENANCE</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="lubricate" graphiccount="0">
            <title>LUBRICATION</title>
            <para>The clutch control components (release bearing, release shaft, relay shaft and linkage yoke pins)
                should be lubricated at the intervals specified in GROUP 10 - LUBRICATION in the CTS-5000 Master Service
                Manual and at the time of clutch or clutch control linkage service.
            </para>
            <para>Some clutches are equipped with pre-lubricated, sealed release bearings which do not require periodic
                lubrication.
            </para>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
